- a holding device (3) for holding a planar support (4) with an arrangement of a plurality of individual detection sites (2);
- at least one light source (5) for emitting light comprising at least one excitation frequency;
- an optical sensor (6) which is arranged such that it receives fluorescence signals (7) from the arrangement of a plurality of individual detection sites (2) and is designed such that it generates computer-readable primary data;
- a field lens (8) which is arranged such that it transfers excitation light (9) from the light source (5) to the arrangement of a plurality of individual detection sites (2) and transfers fluorescence signals (7) from the arrangement of a plurality of individual detection sites (2) to the optical sensor (6);
- an excitation lens arrangement (10) which is arranged such that it transfers excitation light (9) from the light source (5) to the field lens (8); and
- and imaging lens arrangement (11) which is arranged such that it transfers fluorescence signals (7) from the field lens (8) to the optical sensor (6);

characterized in that
- the optical instrument (1) comprises an objective array (18) which comprises a field lens array (19) with field lens array elements (20) and a pupil lens array (21) with pupil lens array elements (22),

wherein the objective array (18) is located in the beam path between the field lens (8) and the arrangement of a plurality of individual detection sites (2), and wherein the field lens array (19) faces the field lens (8) and the pupil lens array (21) faces the plurality of detection sites (2), wherein the beam path of the excitation light (9) and the beam path of the fluorescence signals (7) from the arrangement of the plurality of individual detection sites (2) are telecentric on the object side of the field lens (8) i.e. between the field lens (8) and the field lens array (19), and wherein between the pupil lens array (21) and the arrangement of the plurality of individual detection sites (2), the beam path is no longer telecentric;
- a diaphragm array (23) which forms a mask for the illumination pupils of the excitation light (9) and the detection pupils of the fluorescence signals (7) wherein the diaphragm array (23) has diaphragm array elements which each comprise one or more diaphragm openings and wherein each diaphragm array element (24, 25) is in each case allocated one field lens array element (20) and one pupil lens array elements (22) and forms a mask for the beam path through the respective field lens array element (20) and pupil lens array element (22) and wherein said diaphragm array (23) is arranged between the field lens array (19) and the pupil lens array (21).

